race.comment: EL QASABI (1) is back for a second campaign. Raced twice in the maiden prep and filled a couple of minor placings while never threatening. Trialling very well and looks ready to come back bigger and better. SASSY ABBEY (9) started even-money first-up at Orange but after leading the judge faded to finish fourth. Keen to give her another chance with the blinkers going on for the first time. GREAT HEIGHTS (7) missed the kick and was never a factor on debut at Rosehill recently. Waller-trained filly who can do a lot better in this modest maiden. Market watch on POLYESTER GIRL (8) on debut for the Archibald stable. Half-sister to the dual stakes winner Corner Pocket. Should have ability. FUADEE (2) is a Yes Yes Yes entire having his first start. Did enough in a recent trial to suggest he can be competitive.
